STEPS TO SET UP AUTHENTICATION FOR [GITHUB.IBM.COM](http://GITHUB.IBM.COM)

### **Servers**

Where the API lives  
 (e.g., `https://github.ibm.com/api/v3`)

### **Paths**

Every REST endpoint defined formally  
 (e.g., `/repos/{owner}/{repo}/readme`)

### **Parameters**

What each endpoint accepts  
 (e.g., path params, query params)

### **Responses**

Machine-readable response schemas  
 (e.g., JSON fields, types)

### **Security schemes**

Token requirements (bearerAuth)

### **Tags**

Groups endpoints in UI (Docs, Search, Repository Info)

### **Reusable schemas**

Under `components`

For bearerAuth, go to your profile on  [GITHUB.IBM.COM](http://GITHUB.IBM.COM) \-\> settings \-\> developer settings \-\> personal access token \-\> tokens(classic)/(fine grained)-\> select scopes-\> generate token

 

![][image1]![][image2]

Go to [watson-orchestrate.cloud.ibm.com](http://watson-orchestrate.cloud.ibm.com)\-\> from left side bar-\> build-\> create agent \-\>Add tool-\> upload OpenAPI file \-\> Upload files-\> continue \-\> select operations \-\> connect \-\> Add new item \-\> provide “connection Id” & “Display name” \-\> save and continue \-\> configure draft connection \-\> choose an authentication type (bearer token) (ADD THE TOKEN   
(generated from [github.ibm.com](http://github.ibm.com)) \-\> select member credential/ team credential

If Member credential: Agent will ask every user to input their personal tokens  
If Team credential: One credential you can provide after clicking on Team credential-\> select Connect.
